The paper deals with the computation of mappings using no extra memory, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the relation between this problem and rearrangeable multicast networks, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS) and network science (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents results on matrix decompositions, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DC).
